---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Us - Typing Speed Practice" description="Learn about the typing speed practice mission, the global WPM measurement standards, and our goal to help developers and writers optimize their keyboard workflow.">
  <div class="flex flex-col min-h-screen">
    <Header />
    
    <main class="flex-grow flex items-center justify-center py-12">
      <div class="w-full max-w-3xl px-6 font-sans">
        
        <!-- Section Header -->
        <div class="border-b border-hairline pb-4 mb-8">
          <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans">About Us</h1>
          <p class="text-xs text-mute font-mono mt-1">THE MISSION BEHIND TYPING SPEED PRACTICE</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section Content -->
        <div class="space-y-6 text-xs text-body leading-relaxed">
          <p class="text-justify">
            Welcome to <strong>typing speed practice.</strong>, a premium, distraction-free environment engineered specifically for digital professionals, developers, writers, and keyboard enthusiasts. Our mission is simple: to provide the ultimate minimalist training canvas where users can build visual focus, train typing dexterity, and reach their absolute <strong>fastest typing speed</strong>.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink font-mono mt-8 uppercase tracking-wide">Why Keyboard Fluency Matters</h2>
          <p class="text-justify">
            For individuals who spend their working hours in front of a computer, the keyboard is the fundamental bottleneck between thought and digital creation. Increasing your average typing speed from 40 words per minute to 80 words per minute effectively cuts your writing and coding input time in half. Over the course of a year, this improvement saves hundreds of hours of manual labor, leaving you more time to think, debug, design, and create.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink font-mono mt-8 uppercase tracking-wide">Our Core Pillars</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-3">
            <li>
              <strong>Distraction-Free Design:</strong> Drawing inspiration from sleek developer platforms, we eliminate flashy banner ads, clutter, and unneeded widgets to ensure your attention remains fixed on target letters and peripheral timers.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Professional Code Modes:</strong> Standard typing test sites only offer prose vocabulary. We provide specialized syntax challenges in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Python to help programmers build fluid finger memory for brackets, symbols, and operators.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Advanced Typo Blocking:</strong> We understand that accuracy is the bedrock of speed. Our customizable error-handling mode supports both free-flowing typing and strict correction mode, preventing developers from cultivating bad typing habits.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink font-mono mt-8 uppercase tracking-wide">The standard</h2>
          <p class="text-justify">
            We adhere strictly to the global typing standard: <strong>1 Word = 5 Keystrokes</strong> (which includes spaces, returns, and punctuation marks). This guarantees that your calculated Words Per Minute (WPM) benchmark is statistically objective and directly comparable to international assessments.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </main>
    
    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
